HEADWORD: Blissful
<hw>Bliss"ful</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Full of,
characterized by, or causing, joy and felicity; happy in the highest
degree.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Blissful</xex> solitude.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Milton.</au> -- <wordforms><wf>Bliss"ful*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Bliss"ful*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Blissless</ent>⟦br⟧
